          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>Kingston Jamaica</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="align(right)"><date>19<hi rend="sup">th</hi> April
                                                  5610</date>.</p>
                              <p>My dear Sir,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">I duly received the<lb/> two parcels containing
                                        the <date>Jany</date>. <date>Feby</date><lb/> &amp;
                                                  <date>March</date> Nos. of the “Occident”
                                        to-<lb/>=gether with your communications<lb/> accompanying
                                        them. I have col=<lb/>=lected the subscriptions and
                                        paid<lb/> your draft on me in favor of “<persName>Miss<lb/>
                                                  Peixotto</persName>. The <persName>Revd. Mr.
                                                  Jacob</persName> has<lb/> declined continuing as a
                                        subscriber on<lb/> the plea “that the Occident was of<lb/>
                                        “no use to him.” I have however<lb/> to request that you
                                        will still send<lb/> over the same quantity having<lb/>
                                        procured another subscriber (<persName>Mr. J M<lb/>
                                                  Lawrence</persName>) who also requiring the
                                        5th<lb/> 6<hi rend="sup">th</hi> &amp; 7<hi rend="sup"
                                                  >th</hi> volumes <hi rend="underline">Bound</hi>.
                                        Be good<lb/> enough to let me know the cost<lb/>
                                        thereof.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">You are aware of <persName>Mr.
                                        Nathans</persName><lb/> appointment as <add>חזן</add> of
                                                  <placeName>New Orleans</placeName></p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>for which city he will leave on<lb/>
                                        <date>Sunday Evening the 21<hi rend="sup">st</hi></date> in
                                        the “Great<lb/> Western” via
                                                  <placeName><sic>Havanna</sic></placeName>. I
                                        have<lb/> resigned the mastership of the<lb/> Hebrew
                                        National Institution, and<lb/> taken the Academy of
                                                  <persName>Mr. N</persName> who<lb/> has kindly
                                        handed it over to me<lb/> since the <date>1<hi rend="sup"
                                                  >st</hi> April</date>. In consequence<lb/> of this
                                        step, I must, (for the present<lb/> at least)—abandon the
                                        idea of<lb/> quitting <placeName>Jamaica</placeName>.
                                        Notwithstanding,—<lb/> my sincere thanks are due to you<lb/>
                                        for the kind attention you have<lb/> shown in furnishing me
                                        with<lb/> confirmation and advice, relative to<lb/>
                                        ministerial situations in the <placeName>U.
                                        S.</placeName><lb/> I have devoted my entire attention<lb/>
                                        to the Portuguese Minhag, and, without<lb/> vanity I have
                                        profited so well by<lb/>
                                        <persName>Hasan Lopez's</persName> tuition<add>?</add> that
                                        no one<lb/> would believe that I had been<lb/> attached to a
                                        German Congregation. Of<lb/> course, I officiate as a
                                        Portuguese Hazan<lb/> in <placeName>Spanish
                                        Town</placeName>, from which congregation<lb/> I have
                                        received several addresses &amp;</p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>testimonials, <add>?</add>
                                        <hi rend="underline">two</hi> from the<lb/> Director of the
                                        Hebrew National Insti=<lb/>=tution since my resignation.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Synagogue affairs in
                                                  <placeName>Jamaica</placeName><lb/>—I regret to
                                        state—are not in a<lb/> flourishing condition. There
                                        seems<lb/> to be a feeling rising in
                                                  <placeName>Falmouth</placeName><lb/> to establish
                                        a synagogue there. The<lb/> Jewish Community in that town
                                        numbers<lb/> about Seventy Souls who are, with<lb/> scarcely
                                        an exception, in good circum=<lb/>=stances. Perhaps you will
                                        lend your<lb/> pen towards stimulating them in the<lb/>
                                        “good <sic>cauce</sic>.”</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">The administration for the<lb/> “School” lately
                                        elected is</p>
                              <list type="simple">
                                        <head/>
                                        <item rend="indent(2)"><persName>P
                                                  Laurence</persName>   President</item>
                                        <item rend="indent(2)"><persName>G
                                                  Delgado</persName>   Vice</item>
                                        <item rend="indent(2)"><persName>Alex
                                                  Aria</persName>     Treas.</item>
                              </list>
                              <p/>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">The number of Directors not being<lb/> yet
                                        complete, I am unable to send<lb/> you a perfect list. I
                                        will however<lb/> do so at a future period (Dr.)</p>
                              <p rend="indent(5)">With best wishes.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(6)">Believe me</p>
                              <p rend="indent(7)">Yours Very Truly</p>
                              <p rend="indent(7)"><persName role="author">Henry S.
                                        Jacobs</persName>.</p>
